      "level": 1,
      "text": "Interior Light Structure Description - Control/Function"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Interior Light Control"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The following control functions are available depending on the input signal of each switch and the vehicle status."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In the initial state when the power is connected, the system detects and controls the open/close status of each door from each door switch without being affected by the state of the ignition switch."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "input signal",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Vehicle Condition",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "output (e.g. of dynamo)",
            "colspan": 2,
            "header": true
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Door switches for each seat"
          },
          {
            "text": "Ignition switch"
          },
          {
            "text": "pre-entry state"
          },
          {
            "text": "post-entry activation"
          }
